<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Lore">Lore</span></h2>
<div style="vertical-align:center"><a href="/wiki/File:Warcraft_Wiki_icon.png" class="image"><img alt="Warcraft Wiki icon.png" src="/images/thumb/8/89/Warcraft_Wiki_icon.png/24px-Warcraft_Wiki_icon.png" decoding="async" loading="lazy" width="24" height="24" data-file-width="400" data-file-height="400" /></a><span style="border-top: 2px solid #b3975f; border-bottom: 2px solid #b3975f; font-size: 0.85em; padding: 0.2em 0.2em;"><i>This section uses content from the <a class="external text" href="https://warcraft.wiki.gg/">Warcraft Wiki</a>.</i></span></div>
<dl><dd><i>The Arathi Basin is one of the main staging points of war between the humans and the Forsaken in Azeroth. Arathi Basin is a 15 vs 15 domination battleground, where each side attempts to control the Stables, Blacksmith, Mine, Lumbermill and Farm for as long as possible. The Defilers' elite troopers seek to sever the vital connection between the humans and their dwarven allies to the south. Meanwhile, the League of Arathor seek to reclaim lost lands for their benefactors in Stormwind.</i></dd></dl>
<p class="mw-empty-elt"> 
</p>
<h2><span class="mw-headline" id="Trivia">Trivia</span></h2>
<ul><li>The  artwork for this card comes from the <i><a href="/wiki/World_of_Warcraft_Trading_Card_Game" title="World of Warcraft Trading Card Game">World of Warcraft Trading Card Game</a></i> "Fires of Outland" series, for the card <a rel="nofollow" class="external text" href="http://www.wowcards.info/card/outland/en/155/Drusenna-the-Vigilant">Drusenna the Vigilant</a>.
 </li></ul>
<p class="mw-empty-elt"> 
</p><p class="mw-empty-elt"> 
</p>
